Legal tenderÂ is a medium ofÂ paymentrecognized by a legal system to be valid for meeting a financial obligation.[1]Â PaperÂ currencyÂ andÂ coinsÂ are common forms of legal tender in many countries. Legal tender is variously defined in differentÂ jurisdictions. Formally, it is anything which when offered in payment extinguishes the debt. Thus, personalÂ cheques,Â credit cards, and similar non-cash methods of payment are not usually legal tender. The law does not relieve the debt obligation until payment is tendered.Â CoinsandÂ banknotesÂ are usually defined as legal tender. Some jurisdictions may forbid or restrict payment made other than by legal tender. For example, such a law might outlaw the use of foreign coins and bank notes or require aÂ licenseÂ to performÂ financial transactionsÂ in a foreign currency.

Generally, designation of a particular form of money as legal tender means "that the designated money is valid payment for all debts unless there is a specific agreement to the contrary".[2]Â In some jurisdictions legal tender can be refused as payment if no debt exists prior to the time of payment (where the obligation to pay may arise at the same time as the offer of payment). For example,Â vending machinesÂ and transport staff do not have to accept the largest denomination of banknote. Shopkeepers may reject large banknotes: this is covered by the legal concept known asÂ invitation to treat. Under the law, United States money as identified above is a valid and legal offer of payment for antecedent debts when tendered to a creditor. By contrast, federal statutes do not require that someone who is not a pre-existing creditor must accept currency or coins as payment for goods or services. Private businesses may formulate their own policies on whether to accept cash unless state law requires otherwise.[3][4]

The right, in many jurisdictions, of  trader to refuse to do business with any person, means a purchaser may not insist on making a purchase and so declaring a legal tender in law, as anything other than an offered payment for debts already incurred would not be effective.

Imagine that you are appointed a Principal/Director of a college which is notorious for cheating and poor quality of education.

You find that most students cheat during the examination with the support of the teachers and do quite well in exams. The result of the college has been always more than 90% in recent years.

You are a person with principles and hence you decide to totally eliminate cheating from the examination. You install CCTV cameras in all examination halls and take actions against the students and the teachers who are found engaged in cheating.

The result is that cheating is totally stopped in examinations.

However, the performance of your college dips drastically and less than 50% students pass. This has been a bad performance in recent times.

You now face flak from all sides.

Students are angry because they failed due to your strictness.

Teachers are angry because their track record got spoiled because of you.

Trustees of college are angry because the result of their college has taken a beating under your charge.

This is what is happened with us during distribution of coca cola. And the result is today we are struggling to get our money back.

Dear Team,
I am writing to tell you how much I am in love with your product range. Coca-Cola has been a part of our family ever since I was a kid. Ever since I remember Coca-Cola was the drink made up of happiness. From celebrating being first at the national poetry recitation as a kid to sipping Coca-Cola and making friends in a completely different city, I have done it all. We had a reward system in our family, everytime a family member achieved something we used to celebrate it with Coca-Cola. This was one of the reasons while growing up, we used to look after each other to succeed. Besides this, Sunday evening as a kid was a blast as we all used to gather around the big couch and enjoy a cricket match or two with Coca-Cola. Coca-Cola was the only thing that kept us going, be it the nail biting world cup finish or during a nervous breakdown right before a crucial exam. Today when I live in a completely different city and am a full grown adult, I believe sipping Coca-Cola is something that makes me nostalgic reminding me of all the sweet memories tucked together. Thank you for being a crucial part of my family's and my life. My mother is a far more dedicated Coca-Cola fan than I am. Mothers know everything as they say. She knew I enjoy my glass of coke with lots of ice, she knew my brother loves it with extra fizz, as I say she knew it all. And that's the reason she was the one always pouring us those glasses because she knew the best. As I mentioned Coca-Cola has been a crucial part of our family, be it some emotional family backstory or some funny anecdote about daily life, it was always there. This is one of the reasons why my mother believes in gifting a bottle of Coca-Cola to our extended family along with sweets on every diwali or every occasion because she truly believes we all have bonded better with each other over a glass of coke. I don't usually write out to companies but I had to write to you guys because of two reasons. Firstly, thank you for putting in so much hard work, you have no idea how many late night stories we have shared over a glass of coke, sat at a bare ground at night to look at the stars with coke by my side, enjoyed the family picnics with coke by our side. Thank you for the same. My second reason for writing is, my mother is a huge Coca-Cola fan which I think you have made it out by my message till now. Her birthday is right around the corner and I would love if the team can send in some Coca-Cola goodies/samples (we have always loved the Coca-Cola official glasses but never knew where to get it). Is there anyway to make it happen? I would really appreciate if the team can send some goodies/samples that might be possible. Either way, if it's possible or even if it's not, we have always loved you and will continue doing so. Keep up the great work of making millions happy. Much love to the team.

Dhriti PC
